        "title": "Foreign Office Files for China, 1919-1980",
        "alternatetitle": "",
        "description": "The database \"Foreign Office Files for China, 1919-1980\" contains complete digitized images of all British Foreign Office files dealing with China, Hong Kong and Taiwan during the period 1919-1980. There are six subsections: 1919-1929: Kuomintang, CCP and the Third International; 1930-1937: The Long March, civil war in China and the Manchurian Crisis; 1938-1948: Open Door, Japanese war and the seeds of Communist victory; 1949-1956: The Communist revolution; 1957-1966: The Great Leap Forward; and 1967-1980: The Cultural Revolution.",
